                <lb n="2"/><persName><name key="Claudia" type="gentilicium"><expan><abbr>Cl</abbr><ex>laudiae</ex></expan></name> <name key="Arria" type="cognomen">Arriae</name></persName> <choice><sic>mari</sic><corr>matri</corr></choice>
                <lb n="3"/><choice><sic>lnconparabile</sic><corr>inconparabile</corr></choice>
                <lb n="4"/>fecit, vixit
                <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>ann</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> L, <expan><abbr>men</abbr><ex>sibus</ex></expan>
                <lb n="6"/>X.

            </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Aninia Hilara made (this) incomparable (sarchophagus) to her mother, Claudia Arria (who) lived for 50 years and 10 months.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>The hairstyle became fashionable by Julia Domna, the wife of the emperor Septimius
                    Severus (193-211). </p></div>
            

